    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Track mentions of brand mentions with HTTP / REST API and Discord end to end\n\n**Pattern:** Social Listening · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nTrack mentions of brand mentions with HTTP / REST API and Discord end to end. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Normalize Post Payload → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Slack → Collect All Outcomes → Stamp Processing Time → Tag Pipeline Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social listening without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Improves response time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "1b097fb1-6b80-9b73-8c1b-a9e4a0ebe4f3",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "17c26029-fb5a-3efc-58dc-cdab842c4bc8",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
